Class Metronome

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • tech_demo.Metronome
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public class Metronome
extends java.lang.Thread
    Implements methods to play a metronome, for use with the Piano Demo. Metronome can be sped up or slowed down, started or stopped.
    Version:
    $Revision: 1.0 $
    Author:
    Helion

      • Metronome

        public Metronome(int x,
                 int y,
                 java.lang.String color1,
                 java.lang.String color2,
                 int intensity1,
                 int intensity2,
                 int dur)
        Constructor for Metronome. Receives parameters to locate the visual indicator but also plays the necessary sounds
        Parameters:
        x - X location of the visual metronome
        y - Y location of the visual metronome
        color1 - Color of the visual metronome's first beat
        color2 - Color of the visual metronome's other three beats
        intensity1 - Intensity of the visual metronome's first beat
        intensity2 - Intensity of the visual metronome's other three beats
        dur - Duration in between every beat
